  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For more information on the base models we refer readers to the original work.",
    "We follow Wang et al. (2023a); Xu et al. (2023) to use Dragon+ (Lin et al., 2023) as a retriever.",
    "Dragon+ is a dual encoder model that consists of a query encoder and a context encoder.",
    "We first chunk each context document with 100 words, and then encode both the questions and all chunks independently with corresponding encoders.",
    "The most relevant 5 chunks, ranked by the dot product of the question embedding and chunk embedding, are retrieved as neighbors."
  ],
